Annuities



ABCs of annuities


Allianz Answers


Fixed index annuities


Variable annuities


Index variable annuities 


Variable investment options















Annuities
Simply put, an annuity is a contract between you and an insurance company: You pay the insurance company premium or purchase payments, and in exchange you get benefits only an annuity can provide.







 





Annuity questions?
Allianz Answers.











Why consider an annuity?
Annuities can be a valuable addition to your overall retirement strategy because they offer tax-deferred growth potential while you’re saving for retirement, and dependable income after you retire – in some cases, for as long as you live.
Many annuities provide principal protection from market downturns, lifetime income, an enhanced death benefit, and other options, either built-in or optional and available for an additional cost. Plus, annuities can help you transfer wealth to your beneficiaries.


Learn the ABCs of annuities:



 













Which annuity may meet your needs?
Because no two people have the same needs or goals, Allianz offers several types of annuities. Ask your financial professional which annuity may make sense for your individual situation.







 








Fixed index annuities




offer a level of protection and potential interest based on positive changes in an external index, but without actually participating in the market.
 More about fixed index annuities 






 








Variable annuities




give you the possibility of greater potential returns based on the variable investment options you choose, but they will experience market ups and downs – so you could lose money, including principal.
 More about variable annuities 






 








Index variable annuities





allow you to participate in market gains – with a level of protection against market downturns.
More about index variable annuities






Annuities are complex products that include many features and factors. It is important to understand the balance between all features available with any annuity. You should consult with a financial professional to determine if an annuity is appropriate for your needs.
  Need help finding a financial professional? 
The company behind the annuity matters. Why Allianz? 
The guarantees provided by an annuity are backed solely by the insurance company that issues the annuity. Since 1896, we've had the strength and stability to fulfill our promises. Through bull markets and bear markets, we've stayed true to our careful planning, disciplined investing, and risk management expertise. That's why we're well positioned for what's ahead.
 Why Allianz





